"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/720691","Department for International Development","false","2017-04-21","<p>UK financial assistance to the Palestinian Authority (PA) is only used to fund the salaries of PA health and education public servants in the West Bank who are on a vetted EU list. The list of eligible beneficiaries is subject to a vetting process that includes screening against international and ad hoc sanctions lists, covering a large number of different risk categories including terrorism financing.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/720691/answer",,,,,,"2017-04-21T12:18:04.633Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/720691/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/720691/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-04-13","Palestinians: Overseas Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what steps her Department is taking to ensure that UK aid is not being passed on by the Palestinian Authority to the families of people who have been involved in terrorist activity.","false","Biography information for Bob Blackman","Harrow East","Bob Blackman","70696"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/720692","Department for International Development","false","2017-04-24","<p>Information on the three members of the Independent Commission for Aid Impact’s Board of Commissioners can be found on the ICAI website.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/720692/answer",,,,,,"2017-04-24T16:58:15.05Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/720692/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/720692/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-04-13","Independent Commission for Aid Impact: Public Appointments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what proportion of the Independent Commission for Aid Impact Board are (a) women, (b) from black or minority ethnic backgrounds, (c) disabled or (d) from lower socio-economic backgrounds.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","70717"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/720693","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-04-24","<p>The Prisons and Probation Ombudsman does not have a publicly appointed Board. The Ombudsman is the only public appointee. The current Ombudsman, Nigel Newcomen, was appointed in September 2011 for a period of five years. His tenure has been extended until July 2017 and the recruitment process for his successor is underway. An Advisory Assessment Panel will assess candidates and then ministers will put forward a preferred candidate for pre-appointment scrutiny by the Justice Select Committee prior to announcement.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/720693/answer",,,,,"70477 ; 70561","2017-04-24T10:11:19.443Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/720693/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/720693/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-04-13","Prisons and Probation Ombudsman: Public Appointments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what proportion of the Prison and Probation Ombudsman board are (a) women, (b) from black or minority ethnic backgrounds, (c) disabled or (d) from lower socio-economic backgrounds.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","70725"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/720696","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-04-24","<p>The precise number of IPPs who access accredited offending behaviour programmes at HMP Hull is determined locally in response to individual circumstances as accredited offending behaviour programmes are not commissioned specifically for IPPs.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/720696/answer",,,,,,"2017-04-24T15:10:55.96Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/720696/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/720696/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-04-13","Hull Prison","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many spaces on behaviour management courses will be made available to prisoners in HM Prison Hull serving public protection sentences in each calendar year from 2017.","false","Biography information for Karl Turner","Kingston upon Hull East","Karl Turner","70903"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/720697","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-04-25","<p>The Animal Welfare Act 2006 (the 2006 Act) provides clear offences relating to animal cruelty. One strength of the 2006 Act is that anyone can take out a prosecution. This has been a powerful tool in promoting animal welfare. In 2015, 936 people were sentenced for animal cruelty offences under the 2006 Act, of which 91 were given an immediate custodial sentence.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/720697/answer",,,,,,"2017-04-25T10:13:58.267Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/720697/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/720697/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-04-13","Animal Welfare: Sentencing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, pursuant to the oral contribution of the Minister of State of 30 March 2017, Official Report, column 480-2, on animal welfare, whether she plans to strengthen legislation on animal cruelty.","false","Biography information for Chris Evans","Islwyn","Chris Evans","70698"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/720698","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-04-20","<p>The maximum penalties for animal welfare offences are kept under review and Defra is in regular discussion with the Ministry of Justice on appropriate sentencing levels. The Sentencing Council recently published revised magistrates’ court sentencing guidelines with the aim of ensuring that the most serious cases of animal cruelty receive appropriately severe penalties within the available maximum penalty.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/720698/answer",,,,,,"2017-04-20T14:11:21.51Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/720698/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/720698/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-04-13","Animal Welfare: Sentencing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, if she will consider increasing the maximum sentence for animal cruelty.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","70848"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/720699","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-04-20","<p>The Government has fully considered the recommendations of the European Committee for the Prevention of Torture following its visit last year. The Committee published its report on 19 April, and the Government’s response will follow.</p><p>The practice of successive Governments has to been to permit the publication of the Committee’s reports of its visits, and to encourage other member States to do likewise.</p>","North East Hertfordshire","Sir Oliver Heald","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/720699/answer",,,,,"70641","2017-04-20T15:00:29.547Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/720699/answer","Biography information for Sir Oliver Heald","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/720699/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-04-13","European Committee for the Prevention of Torture and Inhuman or Degrading Treatment or Punishment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what assessment has she made of the implications for her Department's policies of the report of the European Committee for the Prevention of Torture following that Committee's periodic visit of 30 March 2016 to 12 April 2016; and when she expects that report and the Government's response to be published.","false","Biography information for Kerry McCarthy","Bristol East","Kerry McCarthy","70937"
