"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/720701","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-04-24","<p>The Ministry of Justice is not currently enrolled on any trusted flagger programme.</p><p>However, the Ministry of Justice continually works with social media companies to flag illegal content where it has been identified.</p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/720701/answer",,,,,,"2017-04-24T14:55:52.58Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/720701/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/720701/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-04-13","Ministry of Justice: Social Media","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, whether her Department is enrolled on any trusted flagger programmes with social media companies.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","70276"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/720702","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-04-24","<p>We are committed to upholding the principle of open justice as we digitise the courts and tribunals service. In parallel with the development of the IT solution and business processes we are looking at a range of public access options for lists of cases and exploring safe ways for SJP results to be made available digitally. In the meantime, HMCTS will continue to publish lists of SJP cases pending in local court buildings as now and to share lists and results with accredited media in compliance with obligations set out in the Criminal Procedure Rules.</p>","North East Hertfordshire","Sir Oliver Heald","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/720702/answer",,,,,,"2017-04-24T14:57:42.873Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/720702/answer","Biography information for Sir Oliver Heald","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/720702/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-04-13","Magistrates' Courts: Internet","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what progress she is making on publishing online lists and results of cases which are dealt with under the single justice procedure.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","70315"
